question: How many immunizations are uncovered by the payer NO_INSURANCE?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uncoveredImmunizations WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'NO_INSURANCE'^^pl:; syn:uncoveredImmunizations ?uncoveredImmunizations. }
answers:
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
SELECT 
    (COUNT(?id)) AS ?uncovered_immunizations       
WHERE 
{
    ?payer a snomed:payer .
    ?payer snomed:name ?payer_name .
    FILTER (?payer_name = "NO_INSURANCE") .
    
    ?encounter snomed:patient ?patient .
    ?encounter snomed:payer ?payer .
    
    ?immunization snomed:patient ?patient .
    ?immunization snomed:encounter ?encounter .
    ?immunization snomed:amount_uncovered ?amount_uncovered .
    FILTER (?amount_uncovered > 0) .
}

question: Please provide me the number of unique customers of the payer Dual Eligible.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uniqueCustomers WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Dual Eligible'^^pl:; syn:uniqueCustomers ?uniqueCustomers. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?uniqueCustomers) AS ?num_unique_customers
WHERE {
  ?payer a Payer ;
         Payer#name ?name .
  FILTER regex(str(?name), "Dual Eligible")
  BIND(str(?name) AS ?str)
  BIND(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(?str, "Payer ", ""), "[", ""), "]", ""), ",", "") AS ?name_no_commas)
  BIND(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(?name_no_commas, " ", ""), "?", ""), ":", ""), ")", "") AS ?payer_name)
  ?payer Payer#unique_customers ?uniqueCustomers .
}
```

question: How many immunizations are covered by the payer Cigna Health?
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?coveredImmunizations WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Cigna Health'^^pl:; syn:coveredImmunizations ?coveredImmunizations. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT (COUNT(*) AS ?num_immunizations)
WHERE {
  ?immunization a snomed:Immunization .
  ?immunization snomed:baseCost ?cost .
  ?immunization snomed:date ?date .
  ?immunization snomed:description ?description .
  ?immunization cvx:code ?code .
  ?payer a snomed:Payer .
  ?payer snomed:name ?payer_name .
  ?payer snomed:covered_immunizations ?covered_immunizations .
  FILTER regex(?payer_name, "Cigna Health", "i") .
  FILTER (?covered_immunizations = ?immunization)
}
```

answers:
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>

PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT ?patientId ?firstName ?lastName
WHERE {
  ?payer uuid:id ?payerId .
  ?payer snomed:payers ?payerName .
  ?encounter snomed:payers ?payerId .
  ?patient snomed:patient ?patientId .
  ?patient snomed:firstName ?firstName .
  ?patient snomed:lastName ?lastName .
  ?encounter snomed:patients ?patientId .

}

question: Please provide me a list of patients associated with the payer with the ID b046940f-1664-3047-bca7-dfa76be352a4.

answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>

PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>

SELECT ?patient
WHERE {
  ?payer a Payer.
  ?payer rdf:value "b046940f-1664-3047-bca7-dfa76be352a4"^^uuid:UUID.

```sparql
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
```
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

}

PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX ct: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>

SELECT (SUM(xsd:double(?medicationBaseCost)) AS ?total_cost)
WHERE {
    ?medication rdf:type snomed:209880005 .
    ?medication ct:description ?medicationDescription .
    ?medication snomed:has_pharmaceutical_form ?pharmaceuticalForm .
    ?pharmaceuticalForm snomed:description ?pharmaceuticalFormDescription .
    FILTER(LANG(?medicationDescription) = 'en' && LANG(?pharmaceuticalFormDescription) = 'en' && ?medicationDescription = "lisinopril" && ?pharmaceuticalFormDescription = "10 MG Oral Tablet")
    ?medication snomed:has_dosage_form ?dosageForm .
    ?dosageForm snomed:description ?dosageFormDescription .
    FILTER(LANG(?dosageFormDescription) = 'en' && ?dosageFormDescription = "Tablet")
    ?medication snomed:has_route_of_administration ?routeOfAdministration .
    ?routeOfAdministration snomed:description ?routeOfAdministrationDescription .
    FILTER(LANG(?routeOfAdministrationDescription) = 'en' && ?routeOfAdministrationDescription = "Oral")
    BIND(STR(?medication) AS ?medicationString)
    ?encounter snomed:has_condition ?condition .
    ?condition snomed:is_a ?disease .
    ?disease snomed:description ?diseaseDescription .
    FILTER(LANG(?diseaseDescription) = 'en')
    ?encounter snomed:has_medication_prescription ?medicationPrescription .
    ?medicationPrescription snomed:medication_prescribed ?medicationInstance .
    FILTER(?medicationString = STR(?medicationInstance))
    ?medicationInstance snomed:has_dosage ?dosage .
    ?dosage snomed:has_quantity ?dosageValue .
    BIND(xsd:double(?dosageValue) AS ?medicationBaseCost)
}

question: Please provide me the encounters that were related to the care plan with code 698360004.
sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?description WHERE { ?carePlan a syn:CarePlan; syn:code '698360004'^^snomed:; syn:encounterId ?encounterId. ?encounter a syn:encounter; syn:id ?encounterId; syn:description ?description. }
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX careplan: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#CarePlan>

SELECT ?encounter ?encounterId ?code
WHERE {
  ?careplan rdf:type careplan:CarePlan .

  BIND(STR(?encounter) AS ?encounterId) .
  BIND(STR(?p) AS ?code) .
}

sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT> SELECT DISTINCT ?first ?last WHERE { ?procedure a syn:Procedure; syn:code '710824005'^^snomed:; syn:patientId ?patientId. ?patient a syn:Patient; syn:id ?patientid; syn:first ?first ; syn:last ?last ; }
answers:
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
PREFIX cvx: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#hl7:CVX>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX ct:<https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#umls:RxNorm>
PREFIX loinc: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#loinc:LOINC>
SELECT ?PatientFirstName ?PatientLastName ?ProcedureDescription
WHERE {
        ?Patient ?prop ?Procedure .
        ?Procedure snomed:code ?ProcedureCode .
        ?Procedure loinc:description ?ProcedureDescription .
        ?Patient pl:firstName ?PatientFirstName .
        ?Patient pl:lastName ?PatientLastName . 
        FILTER (?ProcedureCode = "710824005")
}

sparql: PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#> PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral> SELECT ?uncoveredImmunizations WHERE { ?payer a syn:Payer; syn:name 'Medicaid'^^pl:; syn:uncoveredImmunizations ?uncoveredImmunizations. }
answers:
```sparql
PREFIX snomed: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#snomed:SNOMED-CT>
PREFIX uuid: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#urn:uuid>
SELECT (COUNT(DISTINCT ?immunization) AS ?num_uncovered_immunizations)
WHERE {
  # select all ?immunization ID
  ?immunization ?immunizationURI ?immunizationValue .
  
  FILTER(
    # filter those that are uncovered by the payer with name "Medicaid"
    regex(?immunizationURI, "urn:uuid.*", "i") &&
    ?immunizationValue = "uncovered"
  &&
    # filter immunizations whose patient's payer is "Medicaid" 
      {
        ?payer snomed:hasName "Medicaid" . 
        ?patient snomed:hasPayer ?payer . 
        ?patient snomed:hasImmunization ?immunization .
      }
  )
}
```

}
